25/04/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The head of the OSCE's Spillover Monitor Mission in Skopje, Ambassador Carlos Pais, says the successful and democratic conduct of Wednesday's (28 April) presidential runoff is crucial. He met on Friday with representatives of the four main political parties in the country: DPA, SDSM, DUI and VMRO-DPMNE. Pais praised their conduct in the first round of elections, which according to the ODIHR, took place in line with international standards, despite minor irregularities. On Wednesday, SDSM's Branko Crvenkovski faces Sasko Kedev of VMRO-DPMNE. (MIA, OSCE press release - 23/04/04)
